quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And recall that We took from the prophets their pledge, and from you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and from Noah and Abraham and Moses and Jesus, son of Mary, and We took from them a solid pledge,"
  33,8,"that He{1}may ask the truthful{2}about their truthfulness. Yet He has prepared for the deniers a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.|2:On the Day of Judgment.
  33,9,"O you who have attained faith, remember Allah’s blessings upon you when troops advanced towards you, and We{1}sent against them a wind and troops that you did not see. And Allah has always been All-Seeing of what <span class=""h"">you do<sup foot_note=""80859"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.
  33,10,"When they came upon you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>from above you and from beneath you, and when sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>swerved and hearts reached the larynges, and you assume{1}about Allah various assumptions.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense, which serves to create a vivid portrait of past events.
  33,11,"There and then the believers were tested and were made to quake with a severe earthquake,"
  33,12,"as the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is sickness say, “Allah and His Messenger promised us nothing but a deception.”"
  33,13,"Recall, too, when a faction of them said, “O people of Yathrib, there is no <span class=""h"">staying<sup foot_note=""80861"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>for you here, so retreat.” And a group of them ask<a class=""sup""><sup>f </sup></a>the Prophet to excuse them, saying, “Indeed, our houses are exposed,” although they are not exposed, but they want nothing but to flee."
  33,14,"And had it{1}been invaded from all its sides, then they were asked tribulation, they would have <span class=""h"">brought it<sup foot_note=""80863"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>and tarried not but a little.",footnotes:1:The city of Madinah.
  33,15,"And certainly, they had previously covenanted with Allah that they would not turn their backs. And Allah’s covenant must be answered for."
